cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.DL, cs.SI 

This paper deals with identifying missing hyperlinks in Wikipedia, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and human-computer interaction (HCI) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with techniques for searching and retrieving information from large datasets. The paper also involves NLP techniques for understanding the context of articles and HCI techniques for collecting human navigational traces, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) categories. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques for ranking the candidates for missing links, which could place it in the cs.DL (Machine Learning) category. Finally, the paper deals with improving the navigability of Wikipedia, which could also place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
